libshapedraw.primitive
Class Color

java.lang.Object
  libshapedraw.primitive.Color
All Implemented Interfaces:
Animates<ReadonlyColor>, ReadonlyColor
public class Color
extends Object
implements ReadonlyColor, Animates<ReadonlyColor>

Yet another class representing a Red/Green/Blue/Alpha color 4-tuple.

All modifiers support method chaining, e.g. Color result = Color.TOMATO.copy().setAlpha(0.4).scaleRGB(0.8).blend(Color.GREEN, 0.3);

glApply

public void glApply(double alphaScale)
Description copied from interface: ReadonlyColor
Convenience method to update the OpenGL state to use this color, with the alpha value scaled by a specified factor. The Color instance remains unchanged by the factor. The final alpha value passed to OpenGL is clamped to [0.0, 1.0].

Equivalent to c.copy().scaleAlpha(alphaScale).glApply(), without the extra Color instance creation.

Specified by:
glApply in interface ReadonlyColor

animateStop

public Color animateStop()
Description copied from interface: Animates
If there is an active animation changing this object's properties, stop it abruptly, leaving things in an intermediate state.

After calling this method it is safe to use other methods to modify the properties without being overwritten by the animation.

Specified by:
animateStop in interface Animates<ReadonlyColor>
Returns:
the same object, modified in-place.

animateStart

public Color animateStart(ReadonlyColor toColor,
                          long durationMs)
Description copied from interface: Animates
Start a finite animation on this object's properties, gradually changing them to match the specified properties over the specified interval.

After starting an animation, using any other method that modifies the properties is a bad idea, as the animation will be frequently overwriting them. Either wait for the animation to complete or use Animates.animateStop() to halt the animation early.

Specified by:
animateStart in interface Animates<ReadonlyColor>
Parameters:
toColor - the properties to gradually change to.
durationMs - interval in milliseconds, >= 0.
Returns:
the same object, modified in-place.

animateStartLoop

public Color animateStartLoop(ReadonlyColor toColor,
                              boolean reverse,
                              long durationMs)
Description copied from interface: Animates
Start a looping animating this object's properties, gradually changing them to match the specified properties over the specified interval. The

The animation loops indefinitely, going back and forth between the original properties and the specified properties.

After starting an animation, using any other method that modifies the properties is a bad idea, as the animation will be frequently overwriting them. Use Animates.animateStop() to halt the animation first.

Specified by:
animateStartLoop in interface Animates<ReadonlyColor>
Parameters:
toColor - the properties to gradually change to.
reverse - if true, fade back to the original properties each time the animation loops. If false, jump directly back to the original properties each time.
durationMs - interval in milliseconds of each cycle, >= 0.
Returns:
the same object, modified in-place.
